In files that ignore unknown or unused definitions (like CSS and HTML), my preference is just to misspell keywords and identifiers by adding an "x" prefix.<p>For example, if you have a block:
    .mystyle {
        font-size: smaller;
        . . . 
    }<p>You can virtually comment-out the whole thing with one extra character:
    .xmystyle {
        font-size: smaller;
        . . . 
    }<p>This also works to kill just one property:
    .mystyle {
        xfont-size: smaller;
        . . . 
    }<p>It applies to HTML attributes too, e.g. <mytag class="abc"> could be disabled with <mytag class="xabc">, which is much simpler than any hack to comment-out the HTML tags or delete the class attribute.
